 Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["variant of   Anne  , in common use as a given name in most European languages. Among people with a classical education, it has from time to time been associated with  Virgil's  Aeneid, where it is borne by the sister of  Dido , Queen of Carthage. This Phoenician name may ultimately be of Semitic origin, and thus related to the biblical <i>Anne</i>. However, the connection, if it exists, is indirect rather than direct."],"variants":[{"name":"Anne","meanings":["Pet form of   Ann   or   Anne ."]}]},{"name":"Katerinia","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of   Katherine .  This is a popular form in Russia, which is also occasionally used in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[{"name":"Katherine","meanings":["Pet form of   Christopher ;  also of   Katherine   and its variants. In the medieval period it was a pet form of   Christian   and   Christiana ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1356704,"age":2,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"description":"Britain waged wars against the Dutch.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1356705,"age":4,"year":"1602","julianDay":2306179,"description":"\"The United East India Company (V.O.C.), destined to become a powerful force in Holland's \"\"Golden Age\"\"of discovery, exploration, and trade, is founded.\"","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1356707,"age":11,"year":"1609","julianDay":2308736,"description":"\"English navigator Henry Hudson, under contract to the United East India Company, sails from Amsterdam and \"\"discovers\"\"Manhattan Island and the future site of New York.\"","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1356708,"age":11,"year":"1609","julianDay":2308736,"description":"Henry Hudson sailed into the river that now bears his name. English explorer Henry Hudson sailed into the river that now bears his name. Hudson sailed for the Dutch East India Company in search of the Northwest Passage, a water route linkin